sequenceDiagram
    participant User as Data Scientist<br/>(Jupyter Workbench)
    participant SDK as CodeFlare SDK<br/>(Python Library)
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API Server<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant CFOp as CodeFlare Operator<br/>(AppWrapper Controller)
    participant KubeRay as KubeRay Operator
    participant RayHead as Ray Head Node<br/>8265/TCP HTTP + 10001/TCP gRPC

    Note over User,RayHead: Flow 1: Cluster Creation (with AppWrapper)

    User->>SDK: Cluster(ClusterConfiguration(...))
    SDK->>K8sAPI: Check RayCluster CRD exists<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    K8sAPI-->>SDK: CRD available
    SDK->>K8sAPI: List LocalQueues (kueue.x-k8s.io)<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    K8sAPI-->>SDK: Default LocalQueue name
    SDK->>SDK: Generate RayCluster YAML<br/>from base-template.yaml +<br/>ClusterConfiguration
    SDK->>SDK: Wrap in AppWrapper CR<br/>+ inject Kueue labels
    SDK->>K8sAPI: Create AppWrapper CR<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    K8sAPI-->>SDK: AppWrapper created
    K8sAPI->>CFOp: AppWrapper reconciliation
    CFOp->>KubeRay: Unwrap → RayCluster CR
    KubeRay->>K8sAPI: Create head/worker Pods,<br/>Services, ConfigMaps

    Note over User,RayHead: Flow 2: Job Submission

    User->>SDK: cluster.job_client.submit_job(...)
    SDK->>K8sAPI: List Routes/Ingresses<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    K8sAPI-->>SDK: Ray Dashboard URL
    SDK->>RayHead: POST job submission<br/>443/TCP HTTPS (via Route)<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    RayHead-->>SDK: Job ID
    SDK->>RayHead: GET job status/logs<br/>443/TCP HTTPS (via Route)<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    RayHead-->>SDK: Status + logs
    SDK-->>User: Job results

    Note over User,RayHead: Flow 3: TLS Certificate Generation

    User->>SDK: cluster.generate_tls_cert()
    SDK->>K8sAPI: Read {cluster}-ca-secret-*<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    K8sAPI-->>SDK: CA cert + key
    SDK->>SDK: Generate client cert/key<br/>(cryptography library)
    SDK->>SDK: Write tls-{cluster}-{ns}/<br/>to local filesystem
    SDK->>SDK: Set RAY_USE_TLS=1<br/>RAY_TLS_SERVER_CERT=...<br/>RAY_TLS_CA_CERT=...
    SDK->>RayHead: Connect via Ray Client<br/>10001/TCP gRPC mTLS<br/>Auth: Client TLS cert
    RayHead-->>SDK: Interactive Ray session
